# ohm. Product And Algorithm Rules

## Core Philosophy

This system optimizes for resonance, not topic similarity.

Goal:

- surface thoughts that meet at the level of human tension
- preserve creative collision
- make one-on-one human encounter easier to find

## Product Rules

- Three screens only: Worlds, Conversations, Me
- Post a thought. Someone replies. You accept. You talk.
- No likes, follows, reacts, counts, or popularity loops
- Replies stay pending until accepted
- Ignore is silent
- Dormancy is valid

## Feed Rules

- Retrieval over stored embeddings, not live LLM feed composition
- Primary signal is resonance
- Replies matter more than passive viewing
- Wild cards must remain in the system
- Never collapse into topic silos or chronology-first ranking

## Data Rules

- Internal interests may exist only as cold-start text
- Do not expose interests as visible taxonomy or profile decoration
- Crossings are private profile artifacts
- Shifts may appear in Worlds while the thread stays private

## Runtime Compatibility

- The LLM now generates a resonance signature JSON payload
- The existing `question_embedding` column currently stores the primary resonance embedding
- `quality_score` currently behaves as an openness-weighted score
